receive $100 to $3000 in grants typically if selected for a summer session grant award the student will receive $150 per unit although there may be larger awards for special circumstances units must be transferable eligibility undergraduates with a declared major or academic interest in engineering who plan to complete courses during the summer session and use them towards graduation requirements applicants are especially sought from the following groups women native american african american or hispanic american important the checklists below will walk you through the application and award reimbursement process deadlines included checklist for students taking classes at stanford checklist for students taking classes at another university or college still have questions frequently asked questions documents are forthcoming please wait until 3 16 2012 thank you application your online application will be automatically submitted after completion the application section also contains further instructions note an incomplete application will delay a timely response to your request deadlines for students taking classes on and off campus online application and supporting material sunday april 29 2012 accept decline deadline tuesday may 8 2012 reimbursement material deadline exception those students taking courses on campus monday october 1 2012 questions inquiries regarding pre approvals may be directed to ms darlene lazar student affairs administrator at 650 723 5984 by email to dlazar stanford edu or in huang engineering center 135h inquiries regarding logistics may be directed to mrs marta espinoza programs manager at 650 721 6862 by email to mespin stanford edu or in huang engineering center 135e or tamara winston administrative assistant at 650 723 9106 by email to tamaraw stanford edu or in huang engineering center 135f inquiries regarding advising and course scheduling or questions about four year plans may be directed to dr noe lozano associate dean of student & div